description:
**About Global IFA** 




 The International Fiscal Association (IFA) is the only non\-governmental and non\-sectoral international organisation dealing with fiscal matters. IFA is headquartered in Amsterdam, the Netherlands (Global IFA), and operates worldwide through a network of independent local branches (IFA Branches), currently having more than 13,000 registered members worldwide.










 IFA is a neutral, independent, non\-lobby organisation and as such the only global network of its kind. As a non\-profit organisation, IFA provides a neutral and independent platform where representatives of all professions and interests can meet and discuss international tax issues and developments in the field of international tax policy at the highest level.










 The objectives of IFA are the study and advancement of international and comparative law in regard to public finance, specifically international and comparative fiscal law and the financial and economic aspects of taxation. IFA seeks to achieve these objectives through organizing a global Congress on an annual basis (Annual IFA Congress) as well as (online) seminars at a global, regional, or local level, independently or in cooperation with established partners; publishing various scientific publications; advancing scientific research, including through various scientific incentives and awards; and providing (scientific) support to the IFA Branches and IFA Regions. IFA also disseminates knowledge and stays connected with its (aspirant) members through various (social) media.










**Job Description** 




 Global IFA is looking for a Junior Communications \& Marketing Specialist with an international outlook, a proactive mindset, and a strong combination of creative and organisational skills to join the Global IFA General Secretariat in Amsterdam.










 The Global IFA General Secretariat is responsible for the day\-to\-day operations, administration, communications and marketing activities of Global IFA.










 The Junior Communications \& Marketing Specialist will support Global IFA’s communications and marketing activities together with the PR, Communications and Marketing Officer and assist with the implementation of the organisation’s communication strategy and marketing initiatives in support of its main objectives.










 In particular, the Junior Communications \& Marketing Specialist will assist with:



* uploading and maintaining the structure and content on the Global IFA website and Annual IFA Congresses’ websites, including formatting texts and updating pages;
* preparing drafts of social media content (primarily LinkedIn and Instagram) based on a content plan created by the PR, Communications and Marketing Officer;
* preparing visuals and graphics in Canva based on existing templates and brand guidelines;
* supporting the preparation of communication and marketing materials, including presentations, newsletters, press releases, and promotional visuals and videos;
* assisting with digital promotion of events and programmes, including the Annual IFA Congress and other Global IFA initiatives, as well as the activities of the IFA Branches and IFA Regions;
* knowing Google Ads is a big plus; deliver measurable campaign results is a plus; in this case, proven track record in optimising campaigns is required;
* monitoring basic engagement and performance of social media and website content and reporting insights;
* help to ensure IFA is one of the first search results for those who are searching online for international tax law;
* coordinating with external partners such as designers, developers, or content contributors when required;
* providing general communications and marketing support to the Global IFA General Secretariat as needed;
* performing other related tasks as assigned.



 This position is particularly suitable for candidates at the early stage of their communications and marketing career who are interested in gaining experience in an international organisation.










**Candidate Profile** 




 The ideal candidate should combine the following attributes:









* A university degree in communication or marketing with 2\-3 years of work experience, or a high school diploma (or equivalent) with 5\+ years of work experience in communications, digital content management, or social media;experience managing social media accounts, preferably in a corporate or professional environment (LinkedIn, Instagram);
* excellent command of English, with strong verbal and written communication skills; proficiency in Spanish and/or Dutch is an advantage;
* basic knowledge of design principles and experience using Canva (or the ability to learn quickly). Knowledge of professional design software (e.g., Adobe Creative Suite) is a strong plus;
* familiarity with basic website content management systems (CMS) or willingness to learn quickly;
* proficiency in MS Office, particularly MS Teams, Powerpoint, Excel, and Word;
* preferably a portfolio of previous work related to social media campaigns, digital communications, or website content; knowledge of audience targeting or social media analytics is a plus;
* ability to work independently and collaboratively within an international team;
* attention to detail, accuracy, and a proactive problem\-solving mindset;
* experience coordinating with designers, developers, or external contributors is a plus.









 Applicants must be eligible to work in the Netherlands. Please note that Global IFA is currently unable to provide visa sponsorship.










**What We Offer** 




 Global IFA offers:



* a dynamic position within a truly global organisation and an international team;
* a 32\-hour per week position, with flexible and hybrid working arrangements;
* competitive remuneration in line with the qualifications and experience of the selected candidate;
* the opportunity to attend the Annual IFA Congress, which takes place in a different international location each year, in the context of on\-site communications and event support;
* a flexible, hands\-on, and cross\-cultural working environment.









**Are you interested?** 




 Please send your
 **application, Curriculum Vitae, and a list of referees** 
 to:




**info@ifa.nl, with a Subject: Junior Communications \& Marketing Specialist – CV** 




 Shortlisted candidates may be asked to complete a short practical assignment (up to 15 mins during the interview) related to social media or website content preparation.

**Hours:** Fulltime, 40 hours  

**Location:** Rotterdam, The Netherlands



**The Position**



As a Commercial Strategy Analyst within our Customer Value Proposition team, you will play a key role in developing and scaling innovative solutions that help customers reduce their carbon footprint. The team focuses on creating differentiated, scalable propositions for VAROPreem that address real customer challenges en deliver competitive advantage.



In this role, you will contribute to the full lifecycle of customer propositions, from onboarding and business case development to pricing, reporting, and strategic initiatives. Working closely with commercial, product, marketing, and sustainability teams, you will translate data into actionable insights that shape commercial strategies and accelerate the growth of decarbonization solutions across key segments such as road transport and marine.



To strengthen our team, we are looking for someone with a structured and analytical mindset, with strong attention to detail combined with curiosity and a proactive approach to solving business problems. You are comfortable working with data and navigating ambiguity in a fast\-paced, international, and entrepreneurial environment. With strong collaboration skills and a passion for delivering customer value, you will be a valuable addition to a team that thinks big, starts small, and scales fast.



**Your Key Responsibilities**

**Customer acquisition**


* Support onboarding processes for new products (e.g., renewable power supply for EV) to ensure smooth transition from contract to delivery;
* Provide analytical support to sales teams, including commercial modelling, margin analysis, and price benchmarking;
* Assist in developing customer proposals and pricing strategies aligned with value propositions and business goals;
* Develop and maintain dashboards and reports tracking commercial performance, customer behavior, proposition uptake, and value metrics.


**Portfolio management**


* Act as custodian of the proposition development pipeline, ensuring initiatives are clearly scoped, prioritized, and tracked;
* Support business development managers and sector go\-to\-market teams in delivering and scaling propositions;
* Maintain visibility on progress, risks, dependencies, and business impact;
* Facilitate coordination across product, marketing, strategy, and commercial teams.


**Strategy \& Insights Support**


* Conduct deep\-dive analyses to identify trends, opportunities, and improvement areas across sectors and customer segments;
* Analyze market trends, competitor offerings, and proposition performance;
* Generate data\-driven insights to support strategic decisions on pricing, portfolio evolution, customer experience, and growth opportunities;
* Assess regulatory and policy changes and their impact on customer preferences, commercial performance, and total cost of ownership (TCO);
* Translate insights into strategic recommendations and support scenario modelling, business cases, and planning cycles.


**Your Profile**


* A Bachelor’s degree in Business, Economics, Engineering, Energy Management, Finance, Data/Analytics, or a related field;
* 4–5 years of professional experience in commercial analytics, pricing, energy/fuel markets, consulting, customer insights, or proposition development;
* Strong commercial acumen combined with hands\-on analytical capabilities and a solid understanding of the energy value chain, customer needs, and market dynamics;
* Advanced analytical and quantitative skills, including proficiency in Excel and data visualization tools (e.g., Power BI);
* Experience working cross\-functionally and presenting insights to both commercial and technical stakeholders;
* Ability to translate complex data into clear, actionable insights;
* Experience supporting costumer value proposition or business development initiatives is a plus;
* Knowledge of customer segmentation, go\-to\-market strategies and processes is preferred;
* Familiarity with low\-carbon energy markets (e.g., biofuels, renewable power, EV charging, biomethane, certificates) is an advantage;
* Understanding of ESG frameworks, GHG calculations, and sustainability reporting is a plus.




**Our Offer**
* A professional and very well\-connected work environment with a young and international team in a growing company, on the cutting edge of the energy transition;
* Contributing to excellent work delivered by the team, where quality and team spirit are key;
* Learn from inspiring and exciting areas that intend to change the way the world applies energy;
* An attractive workplace in the office in Rotterdam with development opportunities within an international, corporate environment;
* Attractive salary structures, as well as a (partly) employer\-financed pension and bike plan etc.;
* Fun and supportive team environment that welcomes you to several social events.

**Are you ready to take this exciting journey with us?**



Then we look forward to receiving your application – simply click on the “Apply now” button to get started.



If you have any questions about this position, feel free to contact our recruiter, Sheila, at Sheila.Berens@varopreem.com.


**Would you like to learn more about our vision, mission and strategy?**

You can



**What are the next steps?**

**Ready to scale your career in a high\-growth scale up where your results drive real world change?**


We’re **Sensorfact**, Europe’s **\#1 smart monitoring platform for the industry**, on a mission to make industry smarter, cleaner, and more efficient. Every day, our technology helps thousands of manufacturers cut energy waste, reduce costs, and lower carbon emissions through intelligent data insights and automation.


Today, we’ve joined forces with ABB, a global leader in electrification and automation. This partnership has propelled us onto the world stage, enabling us to expand rapidly and help more businesses optimize their energy efficiency, cut costs, and make a positive impact on the planet.

**Apply today and help shape a smarter and more sustainable industry.**


We are looking for an **Asset Reliability Engineer** with a passion for **Predictive Maintenance**, who will be our in\-house expert that ensures that our Maintenance Advice is of the highest quality


You will do this through two core activities:

* Give advice to operational teams for challenging situations; installation advice for uncommon assets, assistance for root\-cause analysis or tailored prescriptive instructions for customers. Secondly, you are continuously identifying and rolling\-out service\-innovations. You do this by assessing the complete customer journey; through shadowing of onboarding reps and consultants, by defining and testing improvement initiatives and by training the people to adopt this new way of working.
* Often consulted by our Data and AI teams, to provide guidance in how we can improve our models and to assist in the interpretation of our data.


In summary, you are the in\-house expert with machine learning knowledge who contributes to the development and refinement of our Predictive Maintenance service, while supporting our operational teams with challenging puzzles.

**What describes our ideal candidate?**

* Passionate about innovation and enjoy helping to modernise the industry;
* 4\+ years’ work experience in an industrial setting;
* A university degree in Mechanical Engineering;
* An assertive, self\-steering, customer oriented and innovative personality;
* Knowledge on vibration analysis (or a quick learner) and understand rotating equipment;
* An understanding of maintenance teams (ex. experience in maintenance consulting or as a maintenance engineer etc);
* You enjoy interacting with customers and providing them with advice based on vibration measurements and maintenance operations;
* It would be an advantage if, in addition to the above, you have experience with:


	+ Maintenance programmes
	+ Python


A holder of a completed MOBIUS CATII and higher (III or IV) course (not a hard requirement, you can get those with us as well )


Visit our website and follow us on LinkedIn, Instagram, and Glassdoor to stay updated on our journey.

**Are you** **a BI expert who believes** **a dashboard should be so good that people actually want to open it every morning?**


Crunch builds the data\-driven companies of tomorrow. Dashboards and related technologies are central to that vision, as one of the prime ways in which information from algorithms is delivered \- and decisions are made. We are looking for the person who elevates this to the next level.


**That means obsessing over clarity, design, and the underlying data model in equal measure.**


As a **Senior BI Developer**, you are the person who bridges the gap between raw data and real insight. You don't just *build dashboards*; you craft experiences. You know what makes a data model work and what makes it silently break at scale. You have strong opinions on layout, color, whitespace, and interaction design, and you can back them up. Most importantly, you lift the people around you: coaching colleagues and clients to raise the bar on everything they ship.


In your role, you will combine a designer's eye with an engineer's rigor and a consultant's ability to challenge the status quo.


 **What will be part of your responsibilities?**

* Design and build stunning, user\-friendly dashboards and reports that people actually use in their day\-to\-day work;
* Evaluate, design, and optimize data models, ensuring they are clean, scalable, and fit for purpose;
* Work hands\-on with SQL and DBT to transform and prepare data for reporting;
* Develop a clear point of view on what separates great BI from mediocre BI, and bring that vision to every project;
* Coach and mentor colleagues and clients on dashboard design, data modeling, and BI best practices;
* Prototype lightweight interfaces and apps using low\-code / no\-code tools (think Power Apps, Lovable, Streamlit, or similar) when a full dashboard isn't the right answer;
* Collaborate closely with data engineers and data scientists to ensure the full data chain delivers value;
* Translate complex business questions into clear, visual stories;
* Champion UI/UX principles within the team, pushing for dashboards that are intuitive, beautiful, and built for adoption.

 **Required Skills**


* Proven expertise in Power BI, with a portfolio or examples that speak for themselves;
* Strong command of SQL and experience with dbt or similar transformation frameworks;
* Solid understanding of data modeling techniques and the ability to assess model quality critically;
* A genuine eye for design, layout, and user experience in the context of data visualization;
* Experience coaching or mentoring others, whether colleagues, junior profiles, or client teams;
* The ability to think beyond the dashboard: knowing when a lightweight app, a simple spreadsheet, or a different format serves the user better;
* You are fluent in English.

 **Preferred Skills**

* Experience with other BI/visualization tools (Looker, Tableau, Qlik);
* Familiarity with low\-code / no\-code platforms (Power Apps, Lovable, Retool, Streamlit);
* Knowledge of cloud tools such as Databricks, Google Cloud, Azure, AWS...
* Experience working in a consultancy or client\-facing environment;
* Speaking Dutch is a definite plus. French is also nice to have.

Above all, you should have a sharp opinion on what makes reporting *work* in practice, the persistence to get the details right, and the generosity to make the people around you better at what they do.


 **Our offer**

**First off, you will become part of a steadily growing team** of people keen on applying the latest technologies and techniques in the fields of data science, machine learning \& AI. You will work in a **vibrant, innovation\-loving environment** with the **proper dash of geekiness and love for board games**.

**While you will be able to work both at the office (in Gent or in Rotterdam) or at home, your presence might also be required on\-site with clients**. Our offices in **Ghent and Rotterdam** are easy to reach, located in a colorful neighborhood of each city center, close to a vast array of after\-work shenanigans.


We provide an **attractive salary package** stuffed with additional benefits such as an (optional) company car \& fuel card, smartphone, and other gear. We help you to get around either by car, train, and/or e\-bike. It's yours to choose.


We put a lot of time and effort into **your personal growth and development**, both as a technician and business professional. We provide dedicated feedback and coaching sessions to help you walk the career path you envisage. Expect your own talent development roadmap and the opportunity to showcase your knowledge to a broader engineering community.


On top of that, we do team trips, planned events, ad\-hoc events, anything really to ensure you shine within a thriving team.


 **Up for the challenge?**

**Apply now and we'll review your application,** and may invite you for an initial phone interview. A job\-specific challenge and presentation later, you could be the next BI expert to represent our team!

**About the role:**


At Landal, we’re building a modern, scalable digital landscape that supports millions of guests across Europe. As Product Owner – Tech Core Platforms, you own the strategy, roadmap, and evolution of our core SaaS ecosystem (PIM, DAM, CIAM, personalization, analytics, and marketing tooling).  



You ensure these platforms are not only stable and scalable, but also fully adopted and leveraged by business teams, driving maximum value and enabling personalized, data\-driven guest experiences**What will you do:**


As a Product Owner at Landal your tasks \& responsibilities include:

* Own and drive the **roadmap and backlog** for core platforms (PIM, DAM, CIAM, personalization, analytics, marketing tech);
* Define and execute the **platform evolution strategy**, including **AI enablement and automation opportunities;**
* Ensure **maximum business adoption and value realization** of SaaS platforms across teams;
* Manage delivery via **external/nearshore partners**, ensuring quality, cost efficiency, and SLA performance;
* Safeguard **stability, scalability, integrations, and compliance** in collaboration with architects and tech leads.

**This is you:**


To be successful in the role you have:


* 7\+ years experience in platform product ownership, digital platforms, or tech delivery management;
* Strong knowledge of PIM, DAM, CIAM, and marketing technology ecosystems (SaaS platforms);
* Experience with AI capabilities within digital platforms (e.g., personalization, automation, data\-driven insights);
* Solid understanding of system integrations, APIs, and data flows across platforms;
* Proven experience managing vendors/outsourced delivery and working with Agile tools (Jira/Azure).

**Come work with us, as this is what we offer!**


Together we do everything we can to offer our guests and our colleagues the best. If you participate, we will reward your work with:

* An annual contract with a trial period of one month, whereby we would of course ultimately be happy to employ you permanently;
* A salary between €4\.808 and €6\.869 gross per month on a full\-time basis\*;
* A bonus scheme;
* 27 days' holiday for a full\-time working week\* with the option to purchase 10 additional days off;
* Flexible working hours and the possibility of (partly) working from home;
* Working from home allowance of €2,45 per home working day;
* Training and education options;
* Participation in the Recreation pension fund. The standard retirement date in this scheme is 67 years. The premium for this old\-age pension is 21\.8% of the pension basis, with Landal and you each paying half;
* Possibility of paid additional maternity and parental leave;
* Various group insurance policies, including free continuous travel insurance for you and your family;
* A favorable staff booking scheme.
* A full\-time employment contract at Landal has a 38\-hour working week, which is equivalent to a 5\-day working week. If you have a part\-time employment contract, your salary and vacation days are calculated pro rata.

**Unfortunately for this position we’re not able to support with a relocation or sponsoring a work visa in the Netherlands. Therefore, we can only consider applicants who are already residing in the Netherlands and hold a valid work permit.**

We are looking for an enthusiastic Content \& Design Marketer who can present our message in a fresh, professional, and international way. In addition, you are well familiar with the agricultural sector, enabling you to truly understand our target audience and ensure our communication aligns perfectly.



In this role, you are responsible for developing, executing, and optimizing our marketing activities within corporate guidelines. You will strategically use marketing tools to reach target audiences, generate leads, and strengthen our global brand awareness through engaging content.



You will work closely with colleagues from departments such as Marketing, Sales, and Human Resources to ensure our communication is fully aligned both internally and externally.



Does this sound like your challenge? Then join Oxbo in Roosendaal and make a difference in the world of harvesting machines and agricultural technology!

**Roosendaal**




### ***WAT ARE YOU GOING TO DO?***


* You develop, implement, and manage online marketing campaigns that resonate with our target audience and increase brand awareness
* You manage and analyze our social media channels (LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, X, and YouTube), ensuring growth, engagement, and visibility;
* You set up email marketing campaigns (including Mailchimp) and use additional marketing tools to strengthen our presence and lead generation;
* You create and execute creative social and content strategies and translate them into compelling posts, visuals, and short videos;
* You analyze campaign performance and produce reports that provide insights into KPIs, learnings, and optimization opportunities;
* You conduct A/B testing and continuously identify opportunities to improve conversion, reach, and engagement;
* You create high\-quality content, compelling value propositions, and a strong customer story to enhance the product, service, and brand awareness of our machines.
### ***WHO ARE YOU?***


* You preferably have a completed bachelor’s degree (HBO) in marketing or communication;
* You have at least 2–3 years of experience in a similar (digital) marketing or content role, preferably in a B2B environment;
* You have proven experience with Mailchimp and the Adobe Creative Suite (InDesign, Illustrator, Photoshop);
* You are strong in writing and editing — both internally and externally, in Dutch as well as English;
* You are creative, entrepreneurial, and results\-driven, and able to translate marketing objectives into concrete content and campaigns;
* You can easily switch between strategy and execution and feel comfortable in a dynamic, international environment;
* You closely follow developments in digital marketing, AI tools, and content trends, and know how to apply them effectively.
### ***WHAT DO YOU GET FROM US?***


* Holiday allowance (8%);
* 27 vacation days \& no less than 13 ADV days;
* Travel allowance and pension scheme;
* A challenging and varied role within an internationally operating organization;
* A pleasant and collaborative working atmosphere with room for initiative and personal development;
* Opportunities to follow training courses and further education;
* A role in which you truly make an impact on customer satisfaction and product quality.
### ***WORKING AT OXBO***


Oxbo manufactures machines worldwide. In the Netherlands, this takes place at the Roosendaal and Belfeld locations. This is where Oxbo machines are designed and produced. From cutting and bending the metal plates to spraying and assembling them into a machine that rolls out of the showroom, ready for its adventure with the customer.





With 18,000 m2 of production space, the location where you will be working is a true paradise if you love technology. The engineers design and draw the machines, and everything is made on the shop floor. We have spacious workplaces, everyone has their own tools, and we invest in machines that support the production process. The support departments, such as service, sales, finance, and HR, are also located in Roosendaal.





Oxbo started in 1959 as Ploeger Machines in Roosendaal, and since then we have grown into an international company with customers in 40 countries around the world. Through various acquisitions and collaborations, we now have around 1,400 employees spread across 14 factory locations and 13 service locations in North and South America, France, England, and the Netherlands. The head office? That is still in Roosendaal.

Fugro’s GroundIQ team is building the next generation of AI\-driven subsurface intelligence products. We are looking for a UX Designer/Product Design Engineer to help shape how users understand and interact with complex geospatial and subsurface data. This is a product\-embedded UX role that sits at the intersection of user experience, product design, and front\-end thinking. In this position you work closely with the Product Design Lead, engineering team, and product stakeholders to translate user needs and UX strategy into intuitive, testable, and buildable solutions.
The role is ideal for a strong middleweight to early Senior UX / Product Designer who enjoys working close to engineering, values product ownership, has practical front\-end awareness, and is curious about how AI\-assisted workflows can enhance design and delivery.


Your role

* You own the full UX process from discovery to delivery, creating user flows, wireframes, prototypes, and interaction concepts;
* You take responsibility for defined product areas and contribute to end‑to‑end design decisions, clearly articulating the user‑centred rationale behind them;
* You plan and conduct usability tests and validation activities, interpret qualitative insights and analytics, and iterate designs based on real user feedback;
* You work closely with engineering to ensure designs are practical, buildable, and well understood, applying front‑end design thinking and basic HTML/CSS to support collaboration and handover;
* You collaborate using GitHub‑based workflows as part of the product team;
* You explore and experiment with AI‑assisted design and prototyping tools to accelerate exploration and iteration;
* You help evolve design and delivery workflows as the platform becomes increasingly AI‑driven.


Your track record

* You have relevant experience (around 3\-7 years) in UX, UI, or Product Design within product\-led environments;
* You possess a strong grounding in UX fundamentals: interaction design, usability, information architecture, and accessibility
* You have practical experience conducting usability testing and applying insights from analytics and can clearly explain design decisions and trade\-offs;
* You have basic knowledge of HTML and CSS and a front\-end\-aware mindset and hold a portfolio demonstrating user\-centred thinking, not just visual execution;
* You are comfortable collaborating closely with engineers and product stakeholders;
* You hold a background that includes familiarity with modern front‑end frameworks, design systems, AI‑assisted workflows, and experience owning product areas end‑to‑end, ideally gained in start‑up or scale‑up environments.


What Fugro offers

* A diverse and inclusive working environment;
* Based on your relevant experience, the salary ranges from €4650,\- to €6550,\- This amount is part of our salary range, with opportunities for growth within the role;
* 29 holidays per year based on a fulltime employment (of which 4 are appointed by Fugro management) and the possibility to purchase 12 additional days;
* Extensive career \& training opportunities both nationally and internationally;
* Flexible working hours and the ability to work from home in accordance with your manager and corporate policies;
* Commuting allowance;
* Modern pension scheme;
* Collective health insurance;
* Possibility to register with our corporate fitness plan;
* Coaching options through our EAP (Employee Assistance Program).


Are you interested?


Please visit our Company Page to find out more about what it is like to work at Fugro.


For further information, please contact Stefanie Baldassarri\-Steenhauer, Senior Talent Acquisition Partner, tel. \+31 (0\)6\-114 55954\.


\#LI\-SB1


After you have applied

* You will receive an automated confirmation\-email of the receipt of your application.
* When we see a match, we will invite you for the first interview within a couple of days. Of course, you will also receive a message if we will not invite you;
* After a successful first round, you will be invited for the second round.
* If we are both still positive after the second interview, we will make you an offer, and with that we hope to welcome you at Fugro!

Disclaimer for recruitment agencies:
Fugro does not accept any unsolicited applications from recruitment agencies. Acquisition to Fugro Recruitment or any Fugro employee is not appreciated\*\*.\*\*

**About the role:**


At Landal, we are continuously evolving our digital commerce platform to deliver seamless guest experiences. As Tech Delivery Lead (Web – Frontend Focus), you take ownership of the end\-to\-end delivery of our webshop and web applications.  



You are a frontend\-leaning full\-stack engineer who combines strong technical expertise with delivery leadership. You guide teams in building modern, scalable, and high\-performing user experiences while ensuring smooth collaboration with backend and platform teams.**What will you do:**


As a Tech Delivery Lead at Landal your tasks \& responsibilities include:

* Lead end\-to\-end technical delivery of webshop and web features, from backlog to production;
* Translate business needs into frontend\-focused solutions and technical designs;
* Ensure performance, scalability, accessibility, and code quality of web applications;
* Act as Tech Lead for frontend developers, guiding architecture and implementation;
* Coordinate teams and vendors, including agile facilitation (Scrum Master responsibilities when needed).

**This is you:**


To be succesful in this role you:


* 6–10 years experience as a full\-stack developer with strong frontend focus;
* Hands\-on expertise with modern frontend frameworks (React, Next.js or similar);
* Solid understanding of APIs, backend interactions, and end\-to\-end application flows;
* Experience with frontend architecture, performance optimization, and scalable UI design;
* Experience with CI/CD, version control, and Agile delivery tools (Jira/Azure DevOps).



As well it would be nice if you have experience with:


* Node.js or Backend\-for\-Frontend (BFF) patterns;
* Design systems, component libraries, and reusable UI architecture;
* A/B testing, personalization, or frontend analytics tools;
* Using AI tools in development (e.g., GitHub Copilot, ChatGPT).

**Come work with us, as this is what we offer!**


Together we do everything we can to offer our guests and our colleagues the best. If you participate, we will reward your work with:

* An annual contract with a trial period of one month, whereby we would of course ultimately be happy to employ you permanently;
* A salary between €4\.808 and €6\.869 gross per month on a full\-time basis\*;
* A bonus scheme;
* 27 days' holiday for a full\-time working week\* with the option to purchase 10 additional days off;
* Flexible working hours and the possibility of (partly) working from home;
* Working from home allowance of €2,45 per home working day;
* Training and education options;
* Participation in the Recreation pension fund. The standard retirement date in this scheme is 67 years. The premium for this old\-age pension is 21\.8% of the pension basis, with Landal and you each paying half;
* Possibility of paid additional maternity and parental leave;
* Various group insurance policies, including free continuous travel insurance for you and your family;
* A favorable staff booking scheme.
* A full\-time employment contract at Landal has a 38\-hour working week, which is equivalent to a 5\-day working week. If you have a part\-time employment contract, your salary and vacation days are calculated pro rata.

**Unfortunately for this position we’re not able to support with a relocation or sponsoring a work visa in the Netherlands. Therefore, we can only consider applicants who are already residing in the Netherlands and hold a valid work permit.**

Department Description



Are you a Data Engineer with a passion for turning complex data into clear insights? Do you enjoy working hands\-on with the Azure Data Stack from to Databricks and solving technical challenges with real world impact?


At Allseas, a world\-leading offshore energy contractor based in Delft, we’re expanding our Data \& Analytics team. We’re looking for a Data Engineer who’s ready to unlock the full potential of our data and help drive smarter, faster business decisions through advanced data solutions.



**Your role**
-------------

As a Data Engineer, you will play a key role in transforming raw data into powerful insights that drive strategic decisions across the organization. Leveraging modern technologies such as Azure, Terraform, Databricks, Kafka, and Power BI. You will design and implement complex ETL workflows, and real\-time streaming pipelines with a strong focus on IoT use cases. You will also contribute to building a state\-of\-the\-art data lakehouse architecture using Delta Lake tables.


Your work will empower teams both onshore and offshore to access, analyse, and act on data more effectively than ever before. You’ll collaborate closely with end users and stakeholders to deliver robust, scalable solutions aligned with IT best practices.


Key responsibilities


* Design and implement data pipelines using Azure services, with a strong focus on Databricks;
* Develop and maintain real\-time data streaming pipelines to process IoT data, using tools such as Kafka, Azure IoT Hub, and stream processing frameworks like Spark Streaming, Flink/PyFlink, or Azure Stream Analytics;
* Build and optimize a modern data lakehouse architecture, employing Delta Lake for efficient and reliable data storage and management;
* Create and maintain an environment for Power BI dashboards and reports that deliver actionable insights for business stakeholder;
* Translate business requirements into robust, scalable data solutions by working closely with cross\-functional teams;
* Enforce data governance and quality standards to ensure the integrity, accuracy, and security of the data infrastructure;
* Proactively monitor, troubleshoot, and optimize data pipelines to meet evolving business needs;
* Design and develop scalable, reusable, and reliable ETL batch processing patterns.


**What we expect from you**
---------------------------

We’re on the lookout for a self\-starting, skilled, and meticulous Data Engineer who thrives in a collaborative environment. You have a strong foundation in data engineering and a proven ability to build scalable, high\-quality data solutions. Your expertise in automated testing of data pipelines will be critical in maintaining the integrity and performance of our data infrastructure.


